## Implementation Checklist

When writing or modifying any prompt or output handler for residential takeoffs, verify:

- [ ] Rebar line items use 20-ft sticks with 0% waste
- [ ] Every wall group has three line items (studs + double top plate + bottom plate)
- [ ] Walls on concrete have PT flagged on the bottom plate line item
- [ ] Interior doors are classified by SW/PD/DB/BF/BD/BP/FR/OH, not lumped
- [ ] Roof OSB uses exact sheet count with 0% waste and contractor-adds-waste note
- [ ] Subfloor T&G uses exact sheet count with 0% waste and contractor-adds-waste note
- [ ] Structural sheets were checked for suspended slab / B-deck
- [ ] MDF trim uses schedule if available, defaults if not, 0% waste
- [ ] Shelving and bath accessories counted from floor plan, 0% waste
- [ ] Wall OSB, drywall, concrete, insulation, shingles, siding still have their respective waste factors

